What you need to know:  Brian Kimutai Bett, 28 died in a fierce confrontation with bandits alongside his three other colleaguesSeven other GSU officers were injured in the February 10 incident at the Kainuk- Kaakong stretchThe deceased graduated from the force last yearHis father- Chief Inspector Daniel Kimeli Kiplagat based in West Pokot recalled his last moments with his sonBett’s family urged the government to consider only deploying police officers with more than five years of experience in the force to handle  ‘deadly’ operations